Write an SQL query to fetch the no. of workers for each department in the descending order.
SELECT DEPARTMENT, COUNT(*) FROM WORKER
GROUP BY DEPARTMENT
ORDER BY COUNT(*)DESC;

Write an SQL query to fetch 2nd and 3rd min salaries from a table.
SELECT * FROM WORKER
ORDER BY SALARY ASC
LIMIT 2 OFFSET 1;

Alter table worker set salary of hr as 120000
UPDATE WORKER
SET SALARY = "120000"
WHERE DEPARTMENT = "HR" ;


Write an SQL query to fetch departments along with the total salaries paid for each of them.
SELECT DEPARTMENT, SUM(SALARY)FROM WORKER
GROUP BY DEPARTMENT;

Write an SQL query to fetch the names of workers, salary , department  who earn the highest salary from each department.
SELECT DEPARTMENT, FIRST_NAME, MAX(SALARY) FROM WORKER
GROUP BY DEPARTMENT
ORDER BY SALARY DESC;


Write an SQL query to fetch names of all workers , bonus date and sum of bonus amount received by workers
SELECT FIRST_NAME, SUM(BONUS_AMOUNT), BONUS_DATE
FROM WORKER JOIN Bonus ON WORKER_REF_ID=WORKER_ID
GROUP BY FIRST_NAME;


